  - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py::TestDockerServiceInit -v`\n72: \n73: - [x] **T3.2**: Write Docker availability tests\n74:   - Purpose: Verify check_docker_available returns True/False correctly\n75:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py:19-31`\n76:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py::TestCheckDockerAvailable -v`\n77: \n78: - [x] **T3.3**: Write size formatting tests\n79:   - Purpose: Verify _format_size handles B/KB/MB/GB thresholds\n80:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py:34-54`\n81:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py::TestFormatSize -v`\n82: \n83: - [x] **T3.4**: Write get_image_info tests\n84:   - Purpose: Verify image metadata retrieval and error handling\n85:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py:57-84`\n86:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py::TestGetImageInfo -v`\n87: \n88: - [x] **T3.5**: Write build_image tests\n89:   - Purpose: Verify build with default/custom tag, build_args, verbose, failure\n90:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py:87-180`\n91:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py::TestBuildImage -v`\n92: \n93: - [x] **T3.6**: Write push_image tests\n94:   - Purpose: Verify push with registry URL, authentication\n95:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py:183-228`\n96:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py::TestPushImage -v`\n97: \n98: - [x] **T3.7**: Write remove_image tests\n99:   - Purpose: Verify removal success and graceful failure\n100:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py:230-250`\n101:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py::TestRemoveImage -v`\n102: \n103: ### Phase 4: Integration Verification (ST-4)\n104: \n105: - [ ] **T4.1**: Verify DockerService integration with BuildRuntime\n106:   - Purpose: Ensure BuildRuntime correctly consumes DockerService.build_image()\n107:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py`\n108:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_build_runtime.py -v`\n109: \n110: - [ ] **T4.2**: Verify DockerService integration with PublishRuntime\n111:   - Purpose: Ensure PublishRuntime correctly consumes DockerService.push_image()\n112:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n113:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_publish_runtime.py -v`\n114: \n115: - [ ] **T4.3**: Verify __init__.py exports DockerService\n116:   - Purpose: Ensure DockerService is exported from services package\n117:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/__init__.py`\n118:   - Verification: `python -c \"from agentcube.services import DockerService; print('OK')\"`\n119: \n120: - [ ] **T4.4**: Run full test suite\n121:   - Purpose: Verify all tests pass together\n122:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py`\n123:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py -v`\n124: \n125: ---\n126: \n127: ## Task Dependencies\n128: \n129: ```\n130: T1.1 (init) ŌöĆŌöĆŌö¼ŌöĆŌöĆ T1.2 (_get_client)\n131:               Ōöé\n132:               Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ T1.3 (check_docker)\n133:               Ōöé\n134:               ŌööŌöĆŌöĆ T1.4 (_format_size)\n135: \n136: T1.2 + T1.4 ŌöĆŌöĆŌö¼ŌöĆŌöĆ T2.1 (get_image_info)\n137:               Ōöé\n138:               Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ T2.2 (build_image)\n139:               Ōöé        Ōöé\n140:               Ōöé        ŌööŌöĆŌöĆ T2.3 (build_image_legacy)\n141:               Ōöé\n142:               Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ T2.4 (push_image)\n143:               Ōöé\n144:               ŌööŌöĆŌöĆ T2.5 (remove_image)\n145: \n146: T2.1-T2.5 ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌö¼ŌöĆŌöĆ T3.1-T3.7 (unit tests)\n147:               Ōöé\n148:               ŌööŌöĆŌöĆ T4.1-T4.4 (integration)\n149: ```\n150: \n151: ---\n152: \n153: ## Verification Commands\n154: \n155: | Task | Verification Command |\n156: |------|----------------------|\n157: | T1.1 | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py::TestDockerServiceInit -v` |\n158: | T1.2 | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py::TestCheckDockerAvailable::test_docker_available -v` |\n159: | T1.3 | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py::TestCheckDockerAvailable -v` |\n160: | T1.4 | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py::TestFormatSize -v` |\n161: | T2.1 | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py::TestGetImageInfo -v` |\n162: | T2.2 | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py::TestBuildImage -v` |\n163: | T2.3 | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py -k legacy -v` |\n164: | T2.4 | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py::TestPushImage -v` |\n165: | T2.5 | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py::TestRemoveImage -v` |\n166: | T3.1-T3.7 | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py -v` |\n167: | T4.1 | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_build_runtime.py -v` |\n168: | T4.2 | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_publish_runtime.py -v` |\n169: | T4.3 | `python -c \"from agentcube.services import DockerService\"` |\n170: | T4.4 | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py -v` |\n171: \n172: ---\n173: \n174: ## Acceptance Criteria\n175: \n176: - [x] `DockerService.__init__` stores `verbose` and initializes `_client=None`\n177: - [x] `_get_client()` lazy-initializes via `docker.from_env()` and caches result\n178: - [x] `check_docker_available()` returns `True` when daemon responds to ping\n179: - [x] `check_docker_available()` returns `False` on any exception\n180: - [x] `build_image()` calls `client.images.build()` with correct parameters\n181: - [x] `build_image()` returns `{image_name, image_id, image_size, build_time, tag}`\n182: - [x] `build_image()` streams logs when `verbose=True`\n183: - [x] `build_image()` prints failure timing when verbose and exception occurs\n184: - [x] `build_image()` supports `build_args` for proxy configuration\n185: - [x] `get_image_info()` returns `{image_id, image_size}` for existing image\n186: - [x] `get_image_info()` uses `tag=\"latest\"` as default\n187: - [x] `get_image_info()` prints error and re-raises when `verbose=True`\n188: - [x] `_format_size()` formats bytes as B/KB/MB/GB correctly\n189: - [x] `push_image()` constructs full image name with registry URL\n190: - [x] `push_image()` calls `client.login()` when credentials provided\n191: - [x] `push_image()` returns `{pushed_image, push_time}`\n192: - [x] `remove_image()` returns `True` on success, `False` on failure\n193: - [x] `build_image_legacy()` wraps `build_image()` with workspace/metadata defaults\n194: - [x] `build_image_legacy()` uses `metadata.version or \"latest\"` as tag\n195: - [x] `build_image_legacy()` inherits `self.verbose` setting\n196: - [ ] All integration tests with BuildRuntime/PublishRuntime pass\n197: - [ ] DockerService exported from services package\n198: \n199: ---\n200: \n201: ## File Changes Summary\n202: \n203: | File | Action | Lines | Description |\n204: |------|--------|-------|-------------|\n205: | `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py` | Modify | 152 | Core DockerService implementation |\n206: | `cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py` | Modify | 251 | Unit tests for all DockerService methods |\n207: | `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/__init__.py` | Modify | - | Export DockerService |\n208: | `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py` | Uses | - | Consumes DockerService.build_image() |\n209: | `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py` | Uses | - | Consumes DockerService.push_image() |\n210: \n211: ---\n212: \n213: ## Implementation Notes\n214: \n215: ### Lazy Client Loading\n216: \n217: The `_get_client()` method uses lazy initialization to avoid import errors at module load time if the docker SDK is unavailable. The client is cached in `_client` for reuse across multiple operations.\n218: \n219: ### Size Formatting Thresholds\n220: \n221: | Threshold | Output Format |\n222: |-----------|---------------|\n223: | `< 1024` | `\"{n} B\"` |\n224: | `< 1024┬▓` | `\"{n/1024:.1f} KB\"` |\n225: | `< 1024┬│` | `\"{n/1024┬▓:.1f} MB\"` |\n226: | `>= 1024┬│` | `\"{n/1024┬│:.1f} GB\"` |\n227: \n228: ### Verbose Build Streaming\n229: \n230: When `verbose=True`, build logs are streamed line-by-line:\n231: ```python\n232: for log in build_logs:\n233:     if \"stream\" in log:\n234:         print(log[\"stream\"].strip())\n235: ```\n236: \n237: ---\n238: \n239: ## Implementation Timeline\n240: \n241: | Phase | Tasks | Status | Completion |\n242: |-------|-------|--------|------------|\n243: | Phase 1: Core Implementation | T1.1-T1.4 | Done | 100% |\n244: | Phase 2: Image Operations | T2.1-T2.5 | Done | 100% |\n245: | Phase 3: Unit Tests | T3.1-T3.7 | Done | 100% |\n246: | Phase 4: Integration | T4.1-T4.4 | Pending | 0% |\n247: \n248: **Total Progress: 75% Complete (15/20 tasks)**\n249: \n250: ---\n251: \n252: ## References\n253: \n254: - Design: `changes/AR-024/design.md`\n255: - Delta Spec: `changes/AR-024/delta-spec.md`\n256: - Docker SDK Python: https://docker-py.readthedocs.io/en/stable/\n257: - AR-021 ŌĆö CLI build command (uses DockerService)\n258: - AR-022 ŌĆö CLI publish command (uses DockerService.push_image)\n\n(End of file - total 258 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-024 ŌĆö DockerService Õ░üĶŻģ Tasks\n\n## Metadata\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-024 ŌĆö DockerService Õ░üĶŻģ |\n| Module | `cmd/cli` |\n| Language | Python |\n| Size | M |\n| Design | [Stage ST-3 completed] |\n\n---\n\n## Task Checklist\n\n### Phase 1: Core Implementation (ST-1)\n\n- [x] **T1.1**: Implement `DockerService.__init__` with verbose flag and `_client=None`\n  - Purpose: Constructor initializes verbose flag and lazy client placeholder","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-024/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775876402838,"end":1775876402861}}}}
